<Article
  title="Privacy | ZeroBeatLabs"
  description="How ZeroBeatLabs handles your data. Short version: these sites do not collect any."
>
  <h1>Privacy</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Short version: these sites do not collect your personal data.
  </p>

  <h2>What these sites collect</h2>
  <p>
    Nothing. zerobeatlabs.org and the demo at demo.zerobeatlabs.org are static
    websites with no accounts, no forms, no cookies, and no analytics or
    third-party trackers. The interactive demo runs entirely in your browser;
    the data you edit there never leaves your device.
  </p>

  <h2>Hosting</h2>
  <p>
    The sites are hosted on GitHub Pages. Like any web host, GitHub may log
    standard technical request information such as IP address and browser type
    for security and reliability. That data is handled under
    <a
      href="https://docs.github.com/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
      rel="noopener">GitHub's privacy statement</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>If you contact us</h2>
  <p>
    If you email
    <a href="mailto:hello@zerobeatlabs.org">hello@zerobeatlabs.org</a>, we use
    your message and email address only to respond. We do not add you to any
    mailing list, and we do not share your details.
  </p>

  <h2>No selling or sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not sell, rent, or share personal information.</p>

  <p class="note">Last updated 26 June 2026.</p>
</Article>
